From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 03 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] drm_dumb: use DRM_FORMAT_MOD_INVALID so PVR EGL skips explicit modifier

DRM dumb buffers are always linear, but advertising DRM_FORMAT_MOD_LINEAR
(value 0) in the dmabuf attributes causes wlroots to pass the explicit
LINEAR modifier to eglCreateImageKHR.  PowerVR DDK 24.x marks LINEAR as
external_only=true (GPU prefers tiled), so the EGL image is flagged
external-only and wlroots refuses to use it as an FBO render target,
logging "DMA-BUF format is external-only" for every mode test — all modes
fail and the display never modessets.

Use DRM_FORMAT_MOD_INVALID instead.  The wlroots EGL path (egl.c line 796)
already skips adding modifier attributes to eglCreateImageKHR when the
modifier is INVALID, so PVR EGL receives no explicit modifier and handles
the buffer in implicit/no-modifier mode — the same path that worked when
WLR_EGL_NO_MODIFIERS=1 was set globally.  Combined with patch 0001 which
adds INVALID to dmabuf_render_formats unconditionally, the external_only
flag is now false and FBO creation succeeds.

---
 render/allocator/drm_dumb.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/render/allocator/drm_dumb.c b/render/allocator/drm_dumb.c
index 3333333..4444444 100644
--- a/render/allocator/drm_dumb.c
+++ b/render/allocator/drm_dumb.c
@@ -94,7 +94,7 @@ static struct wlr_drm_dumb_buffer *create_buffer(
 	buffer->dmabuf = (struct wlr_dmabuf_attributes){
 		.width = buffer->width,
 		.height = buffer->height,
 		.format = format->format,
-		.modifier = DRM_FORMAT_MOD_LINEAR,
+		.modifier = DRM_FORMAT_MOD_INVALID,
 		.n_planes = 1,
 		.offset[0] = 0,
 		.stride[0] = buffer->stride,
